ses nor efforts to count heads. Instead, the papers result from the effort to understand training, as it happens inside schools and training centres. But also, looking at a broader picture and asking what policies are appropriate to deal with them as a group.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aAusbildung.  aBeruf.  aBrasilien.  aEntwicklungssoziologie.  aSchule.0 cprintz978387997410840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311240221440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783112402214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783112402214/original  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK